                            <comment id="12828023" author="bayard" created="Mon, 1 Feb 2010 07:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 3.1 as not a backwards-incompatible enhancement, so no need to work hard to get in 3.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13817349" author="jtaylormayfield" created="Fri, 8 Nov 2013 15:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s what I have so far. Basically, the method builds a list of exclude fields from the lhs (&apos;this&apos;) class fields that aren&apos;t annotated and then calls the reflection equals method. This involved expanding FieldUtils, AnnotationUtils, and, obviously, EqualsBuilder. I also included a &quot;default&quot; annotation, although I wasn&apos;t sure where to put it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before I implement similar logic for toString and hash code I thought I&apos;d get opinions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
